area_name: Body Dump Area and surrounding coming soon., The

content.description: When you arrive to the Calvary Men area, you have to climb the Urinal. It is a great warm-up. Start sitting in the overhanging crack, and pull out right on sloping jugs to the right topout.
content.location:
This is on the boulder in front of

The Calvary Men

.

content.description: This ascends a left-angled crack on nice stone.
content.location:
It is West of the

Cavary Men

directly behind the downclimb for

CM

.

content.description: The crux is mid way on the boulder with a safe fall, but after a dead point to a jug cobble, you have to mantle 18 feet off the deck, and it's not easy. This must do problem sees little traffic due to its highball status.
content.protection: You need 3-5 pads and competent spotters.
content.location: From the Body Dump (700e) parking lot, walk along the fence line until you come to the boulder lying just on the other side of the fence. A pretty seam, a big move to jug, and a mantel, this line commands respect.

content.description: The hardest moves are right off the ground. The grade softens as the ground gets further away. Keep your cool!
content.location: It is on the East side. Start on two good crimps at head height. Throw a big right heel, and you're off....

content.description: Start matched in a obvious jug rail. Make cool moves up crimps to a high off the deck crux. This problem is great, but it is not for the faint of heart.
content.location:
This problem is located to the direct right of the

The Calvary Men

. There is a very obvious start. The downclimb is scary.
